<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2019, &ldquo;On the Relationship Between
<em>Psuch&ecirc;</em> and Senses in Plato&rsquo;s
<em>Theaetetus</em>&rdquo;, in D. Zucca-R. Medda (eds.), <em>The
Soul/Body Problem in Plato and Aristotle</em>, Baden-Baden: Academia,
55&ndash;74.</li>

<li>Burnyeat, M.F., 1990, <em>The Theaetetus of Plato</em>, With a
Translation by J. Levett, Hackett: Indianapolis.</li>

<li>Cambiano, G., 2007, &ldquo;Problemi della memoria in
Platone.&rdquo; In M. M. Sassi (ed.), <em>Tracce nella mente: Teorie
della memoria da Platone ai moderni</em>, Pisa: Edizioni della
Normale, 1&ndash;23.</li>

<li>Campbell, L., 1883, <em>The Theaetetus of Plato</em>, Oxford:
Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>Capuccino, C., 2014, &Alpha;&Rho;&Chi;&Eta;
&Lambda;&Omicron;&Gamma;&Omicron;&Upsilon;<em>: Sui proemi platonici e
il loro significato filosofico</em>, Olschki: Florence.</li>

<li>Casertano, G. (ed.), 2002, <em>Il</em> Teeteto <em>di Platone:
Struttura e problematiche</em>, Naples: Loffredo.</li>

<li>Castagnoli, L., 2010, <em>Ancient Self-Refutation: The Logic and
History of the Self-Refutation Argument from Democritus to
Augustine</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Chappell, T.D.J., 1995, &ldquo;Does Protagoras Refute
Himself?,&rdquo; <em>Classical Quarterly</em>, 45: 333&ndash;338.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2005, <em>Reading Plato&rsquo;s
Theaetetus</em>, Indianapolis: Hackett.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2006, &ldquo;Reading the
<em>Peritrope</em>&rdquo;, <em>Phronesis</em>, 51: 109&ndash;139.</li>

<li>Cherniss, H., 1965, &ldquo;The Relation of the <em>Timaeus</em> to
Plato&rsquo;s Later Dialogues,&rdquo; in Id., <em>Selected
Papers</em>, Leiden: Brill, 1977, 298&ndash;339.</li>

<li>Cornford, F.M., 1935, <em>Plato&rsquo;s Theory of Knowledge</em>,
London: Routledge.</li>

<li>Corradi, M., 2012, <em>Protagora tra filologia e filosofia: La
testimonianza di Aristotele</em>, Pisa-Rome: Serra.</li>

<li>Crivelli, P., 1998,
&ldquo;&Alpha;&Lambda;&Lambda;&Omicron;&Delta;&Omicron;&Xi;&Iota;&Alpha;.&rdquo;
<em>Archiv f&uuml;r Geschichte der Philosophie</em>, 80:
1&ndash;29.</li>

<li>Crombie, I., 1963, <em>An Examination of Plato&rsquo;s
Doctrines</em>, London: Routledge.</li>

<li>Denyer, N., 1991, <em>Language, Thought and Falsehood in Ancient
Greek Philosophy</em>, London: Routledge.</li>

<li>Di&egrave;s, A., 1923, <em>Platon: Oeuvres Compl&egrave;tes</em>,
Paris: Belles Lettres. (The <em>Theaetetus</em> is in Volume VII, Part
I.)</li>

<li>Dixsaut, M., 2002, &ldquo;Natura e ruolo dell&rsquo;anima nella
sensazione (<em>Teeteto</em> 184b-186e),&rdquo; in Casertano 2002:
39&ndash;62.</li>

<li>Erler, M., 1987, <em>Der Sinn der Aporien in den Dialogen Platons:
&Uuml;bungsst&uuml;cke zur Anleitung im philosophischen Denken</em>,
Berlin and New York: De Gruyter.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2002, &ldquo;Epicurus as <em>deus
mortalis</em>: <em>Homoiosis theoi</em> and Epicurean
Self-Cultivation,&rdquo; in D. Frede&ndash;A. Laks (eds.),
<em>Traditions of Theology: Studies in Hellenistic Theology, Its
Background and Aftermath</em>, Leiden, Boston and K&ouml;ln: Brill,
159&ndash;181.</li>

<li>Ferrari, F., 2002, &ldquo;Verit&agrave; e giudizio: Il senso e la
funzione dell&rsquo;essere tra
&alpha;&#7988;&sigma;&theta;&eta;&sigma;&iota;&sigmaf; e
&delta;&#972;&xi;&alpha;.&rdquo; in Casertano 2002:
156&ndash;174.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; (ed.), 2011, <em>Platone: Teeteto</em>,
Milan: Rizzoli.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013, &ldquo;L&rsquo;interpretazione del
<em>Teeteto</em> e la natura della epistemologia platonica. Alcune
osservazioni,&rdquo; <em>Elenchos</em>, 34: 399&ndash;422.</li>

<li>Fine, G., 1979, &ldquo;False Belief in the
<em>Theaetetus</em>&rdquo;, <em>Phronesis</em>, 24: 70&ndash;80.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1996, &ldquo;Protagorean
Relativisms&rdquo;, in J. Cleary and W. Wians (eds.), <em>Proceedings
